Parameter.Name: fit_flag
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: Epoch
Parameter.Description: This flag denotes the fit quality and encodes any contingencies in the ion VDF analysis (10=SW parameters OK)
Parameter.Caveats: FLAG values indicate analysis contingencies: 10: Solar wind parameters OK -- no action necessary 9: Alpha particles relatively too cold 8: Alpha particles overlap within protons in CDF. 7: Alphas too fast, out of SWE range 6: Alpha particle peak may be confused with second proton peak. 5: Parameters OK, but Tp=Ta constraint used (params obtained with SUB_PROT=1) 4: alphas are unusually cold, Tp=Ta constraint used (SUB_PROT=1) 3: alpha patr. relatively too hot (SUB_PROT=1). Tp=Ta constraint used 2: The speed of the alpha is unusually low. 1: Poor peak identification 0: Spectrum cannot be fit with a bimax model.

Parameter.Name: Epoch
Parameter.Description: CDF Epoch time at the beginning of each SWE spectrum (milliseconds)
Parameter.Caveats: * The Epoch value is the number of milliseconds since 01-Jan-0000 00:00:00.000 This Parameter exhibits an increasing Monotonic Progression
